<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-104-131 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 049 966</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Desktop Publishing  July 22 1991 v5 n11p29(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Magazine Rack: first mass-market CD-ROM. (Information Access Co.)andO;(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ziff Communications Co. Information Access Co. (Productintroduction).andO;Product:   Magazine Rack (Data base) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Data BasesCD-ROMProduct IntroductionMagazines.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Ninety bucks, 300 magazinesandM;Are you ready to be impressed with a CD-ROM disc that has no multimediacomponents?andP;  The recently released Magazine Rack CD-ROM from InformationAccess Company delivers the full text (but not page images) of articles fromthe 1990 output of 300 magazines, journals and newsletters.andP;  The disc, forPC-compatible CD-ROM drives, includes more than 100,000 articles from fourcategories of publications: general interest, business, health and computers.andM;The breakthrough is the suggested price of $89.95.andP;  Information Access claimsthat this CD-ROM is the &quot;first true mass-market CD-ROM product&quot; because ofits wide appeal, ease of use and reasonable price.andP;  Our experience with thedisc confirms this claim.andM;More than 825 megabytes of text plus a full-text index are shoehorned ontothe disc using Folio's Views and PreViews text compression, decompression,indexing and retrieval software.andP;  The search software supports Booleankeyword and full-text searches, and it can also search by type of article,subject, author, product name, company name, publication date and publicationname.andP;  Citations or full text (or abstracts in the case of a few periodicals,such as the New England Journal of Medicine) can be viewed on the screen,printed or copied to disk.andM;Among the three hundred magazines are U.S.andP;  News andamp; World Report, Whole EarthReview, The New Republic, National Review, The Economist, Science News,MacUser and PC Magazine.andP;  There are also more specialized publications:Bakery Production and Marketing, Coal Outlook, Modern Machine Shop and thelike.andO;</TEXT></DOC>